{{Infobox Union |name = Zionist General Council |country= [[Israel]] |people = Helena Glaser, chairperson |native_name = Havaad Hapoel Hazioni |website = [http://www.jewishagency.org// www.jewishagency.org] |founded= {{start date and age|1921}} }} [[File:Zionist General Council, Jerusalem 1935.jpg|thumb|300px|[[Yitzhak Ben-Zvi]] addresses Zionist General Council meeting in Jerusalem, 1935]] '''Zionist General Council''' ('''ZGC''') ({{lang-he|הוועד הפועל הציוני}}) (HaVa'ad HaPoel HaTzioni) is the supreme institution of the [[Zionist movement]].<ref>[http://www.jewishagency.org/JewishAgency/English/Home/Jewish+Agency+Resources/JAFI+WZO+Related+Sites/WZO/Institutions/General+Council.htm Jewish Agency: Zionist General Council]</ref>
The ZGC was established in 1921 following a decision reached at the [[World Zionist Organization#World Zionist Congress|11th World Zionist Congress]]. It is composed of members elected at the World Zionist Congress and representatives of Zionist organizations. The council has 25–30 members. The ZGC is responsible for implementing decisions reached at the World Zionist Congress and the administration of the Zionist movement.
In 2010, Helena Glaser, President of World [[Women's International Zionist Organization|WIZO]], was unanimously elected chairperson of the Zionist General Council at the 36th World Zionist Congress in [[Jerusalem]].<ref>[http://www.wizo.org/htmls/page_1165.aspx?c0=13907&bsp=13219 Helena Glaser elected as Chairperson of Zionist General Council]{{dead link|date=July 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
